<p>The gentrification wave transforming parts of Parkdale has brought Samsung French-door refrigerators, LG InstaView models, and Bosch counter-depth units into renovated Victorian homes. These modern refrigerators in century-old houses create a specific issue: many Parkdale Victorians still have 100-amp electrical panels with circuits that weren't designed for inverter compressor power draw. Voltage fluctuations can cause inverter board failures in Samsung and LG units — the compressor cycles erratically, the fridge warms up, and error codes appear. Our technicians test circuit voltage as part of every diagnostic in heritage homes.</p>
