<p>Parkdale condo dishwashers also experience a problem specific to high-rise buildings: inconsistent water temperature. When multiple units in a building are drawing hot water simultaneously, the water temperature at the dishwasher supply can drop below the 49-degree Celsius minimum that most dishwashers need for effective cleaning. Modern dishwashers with built-in water heaters compensate for this, but older models without heating elements produce poor wash results during peak hot-water demand periods. Our technicians test the inlet water temperature and advise on whether a machine with a built-in heater would resolve the issue.</p>
